<font color="#FF0000">MISSING CORPSMEN</font><br>
<tt>Sat Jan 17 15:59:13 US/Eastern 1998
</tt><p>
<br>
Doc Jake<br>
Welcome Home, I was going to say WELCOME HOME, but I didn't want to shout on account you might have a hangover.<br><br>
It took me awhile to find over 27 of the 47 Marines that served in 1st platoon, knew only nicknames and some last names but found one, then another and they remembered the names of others and soon it all came together.<br><br>
Doc, you can rest assure that the Marines you served with remember you, appreciate you and think of you often and they may not remember you name, but they remember you. <br><br>
A corpsmen that served with us, I would like to find remember him only as doc mac? But I'll find him, it may take awhile but I will. <br><br>
What unit (Marine unit) did you serve with? that will help. Meanwhile come on by and rest a spell at our company's CP.<br><br>
http://washington.xtn.net/~grunt/vietnam/<br><br>
It takes awhile to load up but has links to other marine units etc.<br><br>
When you come over ahhhh!, well wes ort of have our own deck of cards, on acount the last two corpsmen that I remmember in nam, kept winning at all the card games, gosh, I loved those two, but I don't remember their names, just called them slim and doc.<br><br>
Welcome home bro, <br>
I always wondered where corpsmen that served with us in nam went!<br><br>
Cook Barela, USMC June 67/July 68
